e exploration to avoid duplication.\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Adding Decoding Tests**\\\\n\\\\nI'm thinking it might be helpful to add a test, something like \\\\\\\"decodeReadsFromCurrentByteBufferPositionAndLeavesTrailingBytes.\\\\\\\" This test would check if the Message.decode function can handle a nonzero position while leaving trailing bytes in the same buffer. Looking at how Message.decode currently operates, it duplicates from the current position and validates by adding `position + totalLength`. It also moves the position through the message and consumes the message CRC. I want to ensure this feature is solidly tested!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_hhypqYTEihXTSAvgv37N3Lof|fc_0602d10f7c4ff6ef0169f78831f2a4819180f529bf11793d5d\", \"name\": \"edit\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"tests/src/software.amazon.eventstream/eventstream/1.0.1/src/test/java/software_amazon_eventstream/eventstream/EventstreamTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"    @Test\\n    void messageDefensivelyCopiesPayloadInputAndOutput() {\\n\", \"newText\": \"    @Test\\n    void decodeReadsFromCurrentByteBufferPositionAndLeavesTrailingBytesUnread() {\\n        Message message = new Message(Map.of(\\\"event\\\", HeaderValue.fromString(\\\"positioned\\\")), new byte[] {3, 1, 4});\\n        byte[] encoded = toByteArray(message.toByteBuffer());\\n        byte[] framed = new byte[2 + encoded.length + 2];\\n        framed[0] = 99;\\n        framed[1] = 100;\\n        System.arraycopy(encoded, 0, framed, 2, encoded.length);\\n        framed[framed.length - 2] = 101;\\n        framed[framed.length - 1] = 102;\\n        ByteBuffer buffer = ByteBuffer.wrap(framed);\\n        buffer.position(2);\\n\\n        Message decoded = Message.decode(buffer);\\n\\n        assertThat(decoded).isEqualTo(message);\\n        assertThat(buffer.position()).isEqualTo(2 + encoded.length);\\n        assertThat(buffer.remaining()).isEqualTo(2);\\n        assertThat(buffer.get()).isEqualTo((byte) 101);\\n        assertThat(buffer.get()).isEqualTo((byte) 102);\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void messageDefensivelyCopiesPayloadInputAndOutput() {\\n\"}]}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 6495, \"output\": 1092, \"cacheRead\": 24064, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 31651, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1777829926617, \"responseId\": \"resp_0602d10f7c4ff6ef0169f7882711c881918994621ddd46c4d3\"}}\n[tool-exec] start id=call_hhypqYTEihXTSAvgv37N3Lof|fc_0602d10f7c4ff6ef0169f78831f2a4819180f529bf11793d5d name=edit args={\"path\": \"tests/src/software.amazon.eventstream/eventstream/1.0.1/src/test/java/software_amazon_eventstream/eventstream/EventstreamTest.java\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\": \"    @Test\\n    void messageDefensivelyCopiesPayloadInputAndOutput() {\\n\", \"newText\": \"    @Test\\n    void decodeReadsFromCurrentByteBufferPositionAndLeavesTrailingBytesUnread() {\\n        Message message = new Message(Map.of(\\\"event\\\", HeaderValue.fromString(\\\"positioned\\\")), new byte[] {3, 1, 4});\\n        byte[] encoded = toByteArray(message.toByteBuffer());\\n        byte[] framed = new byte[2 + encoded.length + 2];\\n        framed[0] = 99;\\n        framed[1] = 100;\\n        System.arraycopy(encoded, 0, framed, 2, encoded.length);\\n        framed[framed.length - 2] = 101;\\n        framed[framed.length - 1] = 102;\\n        ByteBuffer buffer = ByteBuffer.wrap(framed);\\n        buffer.position(2);\\n\\n        Message decoded = Message.decode(buffer);\\n\\n        assertThat(decoded).isEqualTo(message);\\n        assertThat(buffer.position()).isEqualTo(2 + encoded.length);\\n        assertThat(buffer.remaining()).isEqualTo(2);\\n        assertThat(buffer.get()).isEqualTo((byte) 101);\\n        assertThat(buffer.get()).isEqualTo((byte) 102);\\n    }\\n\\n  