159     }\\n+160 \\n+161     @Test\\n 140     void messageDefensivelyCopiesPayloadInputAndOutput() {\\n 141         byte[] payload = new byte[] {1, 2, 3};\\n 142         Message message = new Message(Map.of(), payload);\\n 143 \\n     ...\", \"firstChangedLine\": 140}, \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1777829939896}}\n[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating API Features**\\n\\nI'm thinking about a potential feature to validate empty strings, bytes, and lengths in a public API encode/decode context. It seems like the current implementation doesn't cover empty header values, which might lead to functional issues. I wonder if it would be better to focus on the MessageDecoder.feed(byte[]) method since it decodes multiple complete messages from concatenated arrays.\\n\\nAlso, I'm considering the existing functionality regarding message headers, since they don’t seem to allow defensive or unmodifiable handling. There’s also the question of whether mutable headers affect message encoding, which could be a bug. I’ll need to test the HeaderValue.getType method, though it seems like there may be some accessibility issues with the HeaderType class.\\n\\n**Considering ByteBuffer Decoding**\\n\\nI'm exploring the idea of a functional feature that allows a message to decode from a ByteBuffer at a non-zero position. This would advance the position to the end of the decoded message while leaving any trailing bytes unread. It seems vital for public decode behavior, especially for stream buffers.\\n\\nCurrently, existing decoding methods don't seem to treat message positions properly. I think we should test decoding while respecting ByteBuffer's position and limit, ensuring that the decoder works correctly with prefixes and trailers. This needs more exploration to avoid duplication.\\n\\n**Adding Decoding Tests**\\n\\nI'm thinking it might be helpful to add a test, something like \\\"decodeReadsFromCurrentByteBufferPositionAndLeavesTrailingBytes.\\\" This test would check if the Message.decode function can handle a nonzero position while leaving trailing bytes in the same buffer. Looking at how Message.decode currently operates, it duplicates from the current position and validates by adding `position + totalLength`. It also moves the position through the message and consumes the message CRC. I want to ensure this feature is solidly tested!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_0602d10f7c4ff6ef0169f78827b9688191bf1771286db1d56c\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp94gxe6hCa9j11JwxhIw-zSkMm8D23z1_QmFxHDI191Ws9dJ677QFeRV5_ys2pAKzz_Nf6OEbYg3v_OclW7HRITYO1Ncf93RkbiZSWdck-gNpapN4ERr61WYyxYfjATv8H4kxQdk-Vs7Z3w5hMJPTUj7MraA6FBRfUbe-Ybom8FGe65y0OnIeUcxaUus3ua6iTnaP6jVpQoA46QvagtbvPUUoe7iyTYBjExtTWRL1ASwXD-OT_porM6vHkdXyuKD2WBJMWGtrDVXm5C-182pNnV49DYco_48Jkat4eNshs8Sh3HYxApgp6ctBoyXZrdebolWaUL2mgKcWaF7viUV8Oq0sbq6eIcu8uaFOh6Wxd9-OFUnx5VU9xLwhNlGxdQ_bMGPXfN49W_HRJ4XN3g3MyPltim_4-9M5w0HutQ4BolpybW67lIohOSjNhQ_lvYQwOZdiMaVvTpQOXHwF-_o8Io2KYCthtcEU0kr4jFPN_KA-n9WTddjeKcrDR7fVfEZ5KRqfnEzsthiHK6OIFkkFKA0-sKVuolYM6xWcUCD-H8t-LmemD55ec1CaeW8Of2wqriIv0tZkb5iuObk8N2MVuB88y0awE5ooQKaenU7yvr8rhMmuC8K_GKBpBlTVeJy7xFOP87GTApvqZmXC_71DH6O_C7wmX9YXOytTUZUCrbA4GEyKpThI4d77PqH3xHr0SBdOyQ1SvASU_A66_Mqr8d7tLi9N797hZZsnvSMMqrECEupNwg0nx2l2MBTxLHVmTTzmEKEJKmDh5kGFfAqmXhdNyGUNWJuus6GCH188HhS-0hHZhE2d3b5IStPH2skTD1PeTxHNrjYQA7YEQC732HQl7f6wnNtutOge2KrHgIPqI5CbZunybduvfRL2ah0dGxmnRXjIJwoytqD15cGKlp9mjPskGDFs4n9HWaTOEhj07R9129zE3QWcaJ4u3wtL9Fimx1XfH69ftbTGog7boF7jC_xTMspc_IzFJB_f0pm1-NWsspBJAbE8EA2hPrE_FHCVU9cn4f25kfqp2FZ8ueSsMUIdJDQREeqMTMg_-FUOMpKjWcsCf5wep0VguDEu3VspeTOl-H2wt9zNRzvPtAMPK0E6vXwK_TCEIyBWkHF1MW30qKYlnmzWYvJRmC0v8KfOCrgFSDSIrOJp-6a-a8DSpRIN5gG-1TpDGrm7lCCQp4-hpINGcBAC_TVugDsJiTMQM-t_MmMQsBVqjk40V4apU8uvpTV8JvtUkANAPVMf_iHl4PXWe_Kp3-ipScQKo81ElGi_Cq34kuvvaZH6ioc5XuuZCDRgsCemicBVyObtXpUd6Fe--OJYHadoYZTlp8vSNp82H1VnyObI7-v